reviews.review_text: Matrix fills in the gaps Great sounding upgrade to my existing copy.  Thanks to all involved. Happy Holidays!

Somewhat disjointed This final show looks very promising on paper, but a  thorough listen  shows Jerry strugglin' to get in sync with the  band and the  band not really helping much either. The first set start off with Midnight hour and Jerry really sounds sour on it. Bertha is better and Jerry gets louder. The  rest of the set has moments,thanks to Bob saving the set, listen to LL Rain. The ending pairing of 1/2  Step> Promised Land works quite well.

Set II starts off with a  fast tempo Scarlet but it is disjointed the transitions into Fire improves and they  play a  fair  version. Jerry seems to realize this and explodes with a  raunchy screaming  final solo. Samson is standard  fair and then the  big surprise Cryptical Envelopment> The Other One> Crypitcal.

They do it a nice justice and pull it off quite well, Jerry voice has deteriorated once again, but it  is  just wonderful to hear  him sing Cryptical. The Other One is  full throttle with Phil playing his loudest and best of the set, Jerry playing is raunchy once again. The return to Crypictal is sweet and the tonal textures Brent adds on his organ are quite beautiful.

This show features a really good drums> space and may  be the highlight of the set. Mickey on the beam sounds great and  when him and Billy go tribal this wonderful sounding matrix really shines.
The post  space is  tighter than the  rest of the show but it sounds more perfunctory than inspired. I am  sure it  was one long  big  party  this weekend for the boys and it caught up with them alittle.
The Brokedown  is the best song they played the entire night.
Sweet Matrix by Chappy! Another matrix gem by Chappy! Lots of Phil.  All 3 nights of this run were magical......
Of course,I was there! Thank you Chappy.This is an excellent sounding matrix,Listen loud & #dontletgo

All the books they were burning.. This is optimal sound for this GD at the Greeks finale.
Very nice from 1/2 Step>Promised to GDTRFB>Miracle.
The entire That's it for the Other One didn't get many plays in it's 85 comeback but it certainly spikes up the usually Bob played part of the song- especially here for this breakout..
i would agree this is a little uneven at times but they played with a moxy in 85 that they really didn't get back until Brent's 88-90 Swan Song.To be fair you had Jerry's diabetic coma summer of 86 and thawing out 'Ensino Man' Aka-Bob Dylan in 87. But i always felt like 1985 was the most wild and over the top I saw of the band in my time from 84-93 on da bus..
Somebody hijacks the PA like 3 times post drums?
Note: Half Step had just come back at Nassau Spring 85 and I do believe Lovelight was re-introduced East Coast late fall 84. "Turn it into a fire!"
Brokedown "to rock my soul"
